window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The Seven Days Campaign was a series of battles fought near Richmond at the end of June 1862. General Robert E. Lee’s Army of Northern Virginia had routed General George B. McClellan’s Army of the Potomac. Depriving McClellan of a military decision meant the war would continue for two more years. </p> <p><i>The Seven Days</i> depicts a critical turning point in the Civil War that would ingrain Robert E. Lee in history as one of the finest generals of all time. Masterfully written, <i>The Seven Days</i> is Dowdey at his finest—detailed and riveting.</p>"; 
